          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-D"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The D beam energies of this experiment were 1.5",
                "MeV and 3 MeV, and the beam intensities were 13 uA",
                "and 22 uA. The mass thickness of the D-Ti target was",
                "2.01 mg/cm2, and the D to Ti atomic adsorption ratio",
                "was 1.77."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "U3O8 black powder with a purity of more than 99.9%",
                "was kept in an oven (temperature 60 degree) for 12 h",
                "to remove moisture. It was removed and then pressed",
                "into three disk-shaped samples with a diameter of 20",
                "mm. The mass thicknesses of the samples were 0.9724",
                "g/cm2, 0.9742 g/cm2, and 0.9855 g/cm2. The U3O8",
                "samples were sandwiched between two Au flakes and",
                "covered with a 0.3 mm thick Cd case outside. Au",
                "flakes with the same diameter as the samples and a",
                "thickness of approximately 0.1 mm were availed to",
                "identify the flux of the neutrons at the sample using",
                "the 197Au(n,gamma)198Au reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The samples were irradiated for 12 h. The",
                "sample (0.9724 g/cm2) was irradiated with a D-beam",
                "energy of 3 MeV at an angle of 0 deg and a distance",
                "of 3.063 cm from the D-Ti target. The samples (0.9742",
                "g/cm2 and 0.9855 g/cm2) were irradiated with a D-beam",
                "1.5 MeV at an angle of 0 deg and a distance of 4.814",
                "cm and at an angle of 60 deg and a distance of 4.497",
                "cm from the D-Ti target, and aligned with the center",
                "of the D-Ti target. The cooling time were 2.7-43 h",
                "for Au flakes and 3.5-48 h for U3O8 samples. The",
                "measuring time was 14.5 h."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BF3"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The BF3 neutron counter meter was positioned",
                "parallel to the D-beam stream at 388 cm from the",
                "target head to supervise the stability of the neutron",
                "fluence throughout the hall in real time during the",
                "experiment."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The characteristic gamma-rays produced were",
                "measured with a single-ended coaxial low-background",
                "GEM30P4-76 HPGe detector with an energy resolution of",
                "850 eV FWHM at 122 keV and 1.85 keV FWHM at 1.33 MeV",
                "as well as a 30% relative efficiency. Calibration of",
                "the detector efficiency used the standard source",
                "calibrating method, using the 152Eu and 137Cs",
                "standard sources with known activities to obtain the",
                "source peak detection efficiency."
              ]
            }
          ],
